x4codes.shortRef: Jour: Nuclear Physics, Section A, Vol.425, p.458 (1984)

x4freetext: -Measurement of the neutron-proton analyzing power in
the energy range from 17 to 50 MeV
52MeV polarized deuterons
50MeV direct reaction peak with broad lower-energy
deuteron breakup spectrum
Vertical cylinder (7.6 cm high x 7.6 diameter) of
NE213 liquid scintillator at 6 m from the n-source.
Target is NE213 scintillator 6m from n-source.
Scattered neutrons were detected at 2 m by 7 pairs
of NE213 scintillators covering the range from 16 to
71 deg lab.The source-target- and the target-detector-
TOF and the pulse heights in target detector were
measured. Measurement of recoil proton for
2 backward angles
7 pairs of NE213 scintillators (20 cm high x
14 in diam.)
.Data taken from Tbl.2 of NP/A,425,458,1984
.For phase shift due to phase changes in the cyclotron
.for gain changes in the recoil pulse height spectra
in the target scintillator
.for shifts in the tof of the scattered neutrons and in
the pulse shape spectra
